terrible. terrible. terrible. here's why.  several months ago i went to this location to get set up with a cpap machine for my sleep apnea. i i had been previously diagnosed with sleep apnea twice before, but i needed a new machine.   it started off fine. i met with dr. martinez to review my history & explain my situation. she was great. after the appointment, she explained what needed to be done to the 2 receptionists out front. essentially they needed to obtain my 2 prior sleep studies, then  submit to insurance for the approval for the machine. i was also in a bit of a rush since i was moving out of state within a month.  simple enough, right?  i followed up about a week later to get a status update. NOTHING HAD BEEN DONE. in fact, apparently no information was in my account regarding the places they needed to get the studies from. i had to explain everything to the person over the phone and provide the contact information again (i provided this during my appointment with dr. martinez also). the lady on the other end of the phone allegedly took the information down.  i again followed up, this time a few days later. they still had nothing. so i decided to take matters in my own hands. i called one place that the sleep study was requested from. they had the request and were going fax it the next day. i then called the 2nd place. they did not have the request. so, they emailed me the release of medical info form. i filled it out, faxed it back to them. they emailed me the sleep study right away. i then faxed to valley sleep center.   long story short, i did their jobs for them. i wouldn't recommend this location. the receptionists do not stay on top of things.

